msIdentifier.collection: Harry C. Cochran History of Business Collection

msContents.summary: This manuscript is a ledger tracking money owed and paid in the years 1493-1507. The individual or family recording the transactions was probably located in or around Florence; family names of individuals involved include Zanobi, Ginori, Ruspoli, Mariotto, and Arrighini, and occupations recorded include barber, notary, merchant (rivenditore), silk worker (setaiolo), and wool worker (lanaiolo).

supportDesc.extent: 167; 290 x 215 mm bound to 290 x 250 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Original foliation in ink, upper right recto; a nearly contemporary hand has numbered most versos (until fol. 134r) to match their facing rectos so that both pages of an opening have the same number

layoutDesc.layout: Debts and credits of an individual face each other in each opening (fols. 2r-134r); each page ruled for a wide column in the center with three narrow columns on the right for amounts of transactions; verticals ruled in lead

binding.p: Contemporary vellum; L[ibro] Nuovo, I Debitori, I Credit[ori] and letter A in ink on upper cover; lower cover with flap and strap for buckle on upper cover; simple decorative leatherwork typical of Florentine account books; date range with incorrect starting date written in ink by a later hand on upper cover, 1496-1507
